Class DFACacheOracle<I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.learnlib.cache.dfa.DFACacheOracle<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - input symbol class
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MembershipOracle<I,Boolean>, MembershipOracle.DFAMembershipOracle<I>, LearningCache<net.automatalib.automata.fsa.DFA<?,I>,I,Boolean>, LearningCache.DFALearningCache<I>, LearningCacheOracle<net.automatalib.automata.fsa.DFA<?,I>,I,Boolean>, LearningCacheOracle.DFALearningCacheOracle<I>

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class DFACacheOracle<I>
extends Object
implements LearningCacheOracle.DFALearningCacheOracle<I>
    DFA cache. This cache is implemented as a membership oracle: upon construction, it is provided with a delegate oracle. Queries that can be answered from the cache are answered directly, others are forwarded to the delegate oracle. When the delegate oracle has finished processing these remaining queries, the results are incorporated into the cache.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner
